      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 45
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_1_listing_1",
      "firm_id": "sybil_1",
      "description": "Looking for a budget-friendly car with plenty of life left for the right person? This one isn\u2019t perfect, but it\u2019s an honest, affordable set of wheels that could make a great runabout, first car, or little project for someone handy. It\u2019s priced fairly for what it is and could be a smart buy if you want simple transport without spending a fortune. If you\u2019re after something cheap, usable, and worth a look, send me a message.",
      "price": 6900.0,
      "reputation": 0.8,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 45
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Strong candidate for a budget build, shop truck, or dependable project. It shows wear consistent with age and use, but the drivetrain feels like it still has plenty of life left, with a powertrain that pulls cleanly and a chassis that remains serviceable. A good fit for someone who knows their way around maintenance and wants an affordable platform with usable bones rather than a polished showpiece. Priced to move, with clear upside for the next owner willing to sort the cosmetics and deferred items.",
      "price": 5900.0,
      "reputation": 0.5,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 45
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_3_listing_3",
      "firm_id": "sybil_3",
      "description": "Cheap way into a car that still gets the job done. Used, rough, priced right, and ready to move. Great beater, commuter, or backup ride. First serious buyer takes it.",
      "price": 6900.0,
      "reputation": 0.7,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 45
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_4_listing_4",
      "firm_id": "sybil_4",
      "description": "Honest, well-traveled, and full of personality, this car has the kind of road-worn charm that makes it a great fit for someone who values usefulness over polish. It starts the conversation with its lived-in character and offers a practical, budget-friendly way into ownership\u2014ideal as a first car, a spare commuter, or a weekend project with plenty of upside for the next owner. If you appreciate a vehicle with story, grit, and room to make it your own, this one is ready for its next chapter.",
      "price": 5900.0,
      "reputation": 0.7,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 45
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_5_listing_5",
